<H3> <TI>   17,000 Grams of Heroin Burned in Sichuan Province </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    17,000 Grams of Heroin Burned in Sichuan Province </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2306154294 Beijing XINHUA in English 1523 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2306154294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Chengdu, June 23 (XINHUA) -- Some 17,000 grams of 
confiscated heroin was burned this morning at the Pixian Sports 
Stadium in Chengdu, capital of southwest China's Sichuan 
Province. 
  This was an important anti-drug operation by Sichuan 
Province 
just before June 26, the International Anti-Drugs Day. 
  Sichuan Province is a passage and transfer station for 
international drug smugglers. In the first five months of this 
year, public security organizations cracked 531 cases of drug 
abuse and smuggling, arrested 706 suspects and confiscated 
46,300 grams of heroin and 13,000 grams of opium. 

</TEXT>

