<F P=100> Southwest Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Drug Trafficker in Tibet Executed, Others Sentenced </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Drug Trafficker in Tibet Executed, Others Sentenced </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2606132094 Beijing XINHUA in English 1248 GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2606132094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Lhasa, June 26 (XINHUA) -- One drug trafficker in 
the Tibet Autonomous Region was publicly sentenced to death and 
three others were sentenced to imprisonment today by the Lhasa 
City Intermediate People's Court. 
  Qamjig, the principal criminal, was sentenced to death for 
having purchased more than 1,000 grams of narcotics in Yunnan 
Province and resold them in Tibet at high profits. After the 
judgement was announced, Qamjig lodged an appeal. The Tibet 
Autonomous Regional Supreme People's Court reviewed the case, 
rejected Qamjig's appeal and reported to the Supreme People's 
Court of the People's Republic of China (PRC). According to the 
order of the president of the Supreme People's Court of the PRC, 
Qamjig was executed. 
  Another principal criminal in the case was Dojie, who was 
sentenced to life imprisonment. 
  The two accessories in the case were Huang Tinghong and 
Losang Soinam were sentenced to 15 years imprisonment. [sentence 
as received] 

</TEXT>

