<H3> <TI>   Li Ruihuan Meets Hong Kong Entreprenuer </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Li Ruihuan Meets Hong Kong Entreprenuer </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2806104994 Beijing XINHUA in English 1019 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2806104994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, June 28 (XINHUA) -- Top Chinese leader Li 
Ruihuan had an hour-long discussion here today with Kwok 
Ping-sheung, chairman of Sun Hung Kai, one of the biggest real 
estate companies in Hong Kong. 
  Sun Hung Kai and the Beijing Dongan Group have decided to 
invest 300 million U.S. dollars to rebuild the Dongan market in 
downtown Beijing into a modern business center. The new market 
is scheduled to open in 1996. 
  Li, a standing committee member of the Political Bureau of 
the Chinese Communist Party Central Committee and chairman of 
the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political 
Consultative Conference, praised Sun Hung Kai for making 
investment in the mainland. 
  Li also praised Kwok and other Hong Kong residents for their 
efforts in upholding Hong Kong's prosperity and stability, 
hoping that they will work together for Hong Kong's smooth 
transition and its prosperity and stability after July 1, 1997. 

</TEXT>

