<F P=100> HONG KONG &amp; MACAO </F>
<F P=101> Hong Kong </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mayor Repeats Jiang's Comments on Shenzhen, Hong Kong </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mayor Repeats Jiang's Comments on Shenzhen, Hong Kong </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK2906034894 Hong Kong ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE in Chinese 0651 
GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK2906034894 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Shenzhen, 27 Jun (ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE)--A few days 
ago, at a conference of all the city's cadres at or above the 
departmental level, Shenzhen City Mayor Li Youwei conveyed Jiang 
Zemin's comments made on a visit to the city on six aspects of 
Shenzhen's relations with Hong Kong. 
  They are: One, utilization: utilize Hong Kong to help 
develop the city; two, reliance: rely on Hong Kong in moving 
toward the international community; three, taking reference: 
learn to do things according to Hong Kong and international 
conventions; four, making ties: establishing ties with Hong 
Kong and branching out in the hinterland; five, making 
distinctions: distinguishing between Hong Kong and one country, 
two systems; and six, convergence: converging with Hong Kong for 
mutual benefits. 
  Li Youwei said: As the "1997" Hong Kong's transition is 
drawing closer, Shenzhen will play an important role in ensuring 
a stable transition, smooth return, and long-term prosperity for 
Hong Kong Shenzhen is a socialist special economic zone, and at 
no time is it an extension or expansion of Hong Kong. We must 
be clear-headed and have a clear understanding of this. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

