<H3> <TI>   Vice Premier Zou Jiahua Meets Indian, Canadian Guests </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Vice Premier Zou Jiahua Meets Indian, Canadian Guests </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2806140894 Beijing XINHUA in English 1358 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2806140894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, June 28 (XINHUA) -- Chinese Vice-Premier 
Zou Jiahua met with Satish Sharma, Indian minister of state for 
petroleum and natural gas, and Andre Desmarais, president of the 
Power Corporation of Canada, on separate occasions here this 
afternoon. 
  Zou told the Indian guest that Sino-Indian ties have grown 
smoothly in recent years, and China will actively engage in 
cooperation with other countries, especially its neighbors. 
  He said the Chinese Government supports China's petroleum 
industry in its efforts to cooperate with foreign countries. 
  Zou noted that China adheres to two principles in such 
relations, namely, equality and mutual benefit, and long-term 
cooperation. 
  He hoped that Sino-Indian cooperation in the fields of oil 
and natural gas would develop without a hitch. 
  Sharma and his party, guests of the China National Petroleum 
and Gas Corporation, arrived in Beijing on June 26. 
  In his meeting with Desmarais and his party, Zou said China 
welcomes the Canadian Power Corporation to enter into 
cooperation with China in power, mining and other fields. 
  Desmarais and his party came to China at the invitation of 
the China International Trust and Investment Corporation. 

</TEXT>

