  [Text] Beijing, June 28 (XINHUA) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng 
left here today for an official visit to Austria, Germany and 
Romania. 
  Li will travel via Urumqi, capital of the Xinjiang Uygur 
Autonomous Region. 
  The premier left for his trip at the invitation of Austrian 
Prime Minister Franz Vranitzky, German Chancellor Helmut Kohl, 
and Romanian President Ion Iliescu and Prime Minister Nicolae 
