<H3> <TI>   Heilongjiang Acting Mayor Meets Japanese Delegation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Heilongjiang Acting Mayor Meets Japanese Delegation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2806014994 Harbin Heilongjiang People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 1000 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2806014994 </F>
<F P=104>  Harbin Heilongjiang People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Acting Mayor Tian Fengshan met with a delegation 
from Hokkaido Development Consulting Company Ltd, of Japan this 
morning. Led by the former governor of Hokkaido, (Uchiko 
Nagahara), the delegation was invited by the provincial 
communications department to attend the ceremony marking the 
establishment of (Beilong) technology development company--a 
Sino-Japanese joint venture. 
  Acting Governor Tian Fengshan extended a warm welcome to the 
visiting delegation. He said: Heilongjiang and Hokkaido have 
established a long-term friendly cooperative relationship and 
profound understanding. Heilongjiang is a major province with 
rich natural resources. Its economic development over the past 
few years can not be separated from its achievements in highway 
construction. The establishment of this (Beilong) joint-venture 
company to engage in highway design and development is very 
conducive to the construction and development of our province's 
communications undertakings. He expressed the hope that the 
Hokkaido Development Consulting Company Ltd, will conduct 
further cooperation with our province in agricultural 
development and urban construction in Harbin, including the 
building of a subway train. 
  Also attending the meeting were Cai Qi, deputy secretary 
general of the provincial government. 

</TEXT>

